## Key Insights and Findings

- Filtered the **2019 Survey of Consumer Finances (SCF)** to analyze households that feared credit denial and had a net worth below **$2 million**.
- Identified the **highest-variance financial features** to improve clustering performance.
- Applied **StandardScaler** to normalize features before clustering.
- Used **K-Means clustering** to segment households into distinct financial groups.
- Evaluated clustering performance using **Inertia** and **Silhouette Score** to determine the optimal number of clusters.
- Applied **Principal Component Analysis (PCA)** to reduce the feature space for visualization.
- Built an **interactive Plotly Dash dashboard** that enables users to:
  - Compare trimmed and untrimmed variance.
  - Adjust the number of clusters (`k`).
  - View clustering metrics in real time.
  - Explore household segments through PCA scatter plots.
- Demonstrated how **unsupervised machine learning** can reveal meaningful patterns in consumer financial behavior without relying on labeled target variables.
